@dkuppitz I pushed fixups for the issues you mentioned in the JIRA ticket.  When you're happy with this PR, I will rebase.

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP3-639?focusedCommentId=14509253&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-14509253

Was the comment about "a TBD in the description" referring to the "WIP" comments that I have just removed?

@spmallette yes that is the primary difference. I wasn't even aware of the two types of GraphSON until a couple of days ago. It's been a bit confusing dealing with GraphSON in its two flavors and then all the changes between TP2 and TP3. If you think it makes more sense to combine and use the Builder I can do that.

Yes, I couldn't figure out how to add the StarGraph edges without making those methods public. Also extracted out LegacyGraphSONUtility hoping to use its vertex/edgeFromJson but then went with StarGraph. Will see what else of it I am still using and try to bring it back as inner class of the LegacyGraphSONReader I believe.

I apologize for some of the mess. Just wanted to get your opinion and make sure I was going in the right direction. Thanks for the feedback.
